== Third-party attribution ==

`src/engine/tree.rs`, `src/engine/geo.rs`, `src/engine/geodesy.rs`, and
`src/engine/meshopt.rs` are ported from:

    bevy_3d_tiles
    Copyright (c) 2024 Arvikasoft AB
    https://github.com/Arvikasoft/bevy_3d_tiles
    Licensed under MIT OR Apache-2.0

  - `tree.rs` ports `src/traversal.rs`'s tile-tree model and per-frame
    screen-space-error selection algorithm (`select`, `History`,
    `Selection`, `Priority`) near-verbatim; `TileTree::build`/`graft` (which
    parsed a `tileset.json` schema) are replaced by `build_from_entries`,
    which builds directly from an AHNP pack's flat entry list.
  - `geo.rs` and `geodesy.rs` port `src/geo.rs` and `src/geodesy.rs`
    verbatim (region -> ECEF bounding volumes; WGS84 geodetic <-> ECEF and
    the ECEF -> Bevy-world ENU anchor transform).
  - `meshopt.rs` ports `src/meshopt.rs` verbatim: a pure-Rust
    `EXT_meshopt_compression` decoder, itself a faithful port of the
    reference decoder bundled with the meshoptimizer encoder
    (`meshopt_decoder_reference.js`, by Jasper St. Pierre / Arseny
    Kapoulkine, MIT).

Each ported file carries its own header comment naming the specific upstream
file it was ported from.
